Advocates of so-called free-range parenting have pushed back.
A Tough Balancing Act for Free-range ParentingThe arguments in favor of free-range parenting are compelling, particularly because the dangers and fears driving more protective parenting approaches—most notably “stranger danger”—have largely been debunked.
The underlying problem is far greater than the squelching of free-range parenting, whatever its merits, particularly for the less privileged, who are far more vulnerable to this type of threat and coercion.
They were free-range parents not by choice, but by necessity.
He has written on the subject of forfeiture reform, as well as on issues of child protection.